						<%= render 'newsletters/new' %>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<a class="more" href="/main/home#what">Learn More<br><i class="fa fa-chevron-down"></i></a>
	</div>
	<div id="what">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="image col-md-4 col-md-offset-1">
					<img src="/assets/fabriq_emblem.jpg" />
				</div>
				<div class="welcome col-md-6">
					<h1>What is Fabriq?</h1>
					<p>
						The Fabriq app is a shared ownership social network for beaming and accepting reputation tokens, or reps. The more you beam, the more reps that you can earn.  Exchange reps for cucumber water and other goods in the Woodstock Lounge of the Future, at the Healing Garden at Mysteryland.
					</p>
					<p>Beam your favorite DJs, art installations, stages, and find others like you. Create tribes with your group of friends and interact with other tribes.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div id="opensource">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3">
					<img src="/assets/github_logo.jpg" />
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1">
					<h1>Open Source</h1>
					<p>Fabriq is a an open source project demonstrating that your reputation will be a form of currency in the future.  We intend to give attendees an experience of an emerging society with a sharing economy and participative democracy that is enabled by technology. Future versions of Fabriq will allow you to create your own shared groups with their own reps.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div id="how">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
					<h1>How does it work?</h1>
					<p>Reps are issued and maintained on a secure peer-2-peer network called Ethereum. It is likened to a global computer that no one owns and everyone can access. Future versions of Fabriq will allow any group to issue their own tokens, create voting rights, and define procedures for how to change those rules.</p>
					<p>Groups can earn badges they create, interact across communities, and issue bounties for role fulfillment in exchange for tokens. These groups could be a tribe of friends at a music festival, a start-up company with governance and equity privileges, or members of an urban residential building.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div id="lounge">
		<img class="rainbow-left" src="/assets/rainbows_left.png" />
		<img class="rainbow-right" src="/assets/rainbows_right.png" />

		<div class="container">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
					<h1>Lounge of the Future</h1>
					<p>Beings from the future have returned to re-imagine Woodstock with us. They have given us a new social currency using the Fabriq app.</p>
					<p>When the hippie generation imagined a new world, they could not have imagined exactly how it would manifest.  Come see what the future holds.</p>
					<p>Collectively, we create the present.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
